    "details": {
      "biography": {
        "value": "<p><em>This ancient animal-headed pillar is engraved with weathered symbols from ancient empires.</em><br><strong>Animal Headed.</strong> Possessed pillars are carved from enormous blocks of stone to look like animal-headed gods of ancient pantheons, or sometimes demonic figures of zealous cults. The most common are the jackal-faced and the ibis-headed variants, but pillars with baboon, crocodile, elephant, or hawk heads also exist.<br><strong>Hijacked by Cults.</strong> Some such pillars are claimed by various cults, and carved anew with blasphemous symbols or smeared with blood, oils, and unguents as sacrificial offerings.<br><strong>Weapon Donations.</strong> Priests claim the weapons stolen by the pillars and distribute them to temple guards or sell them to fund temple activities.<br><strong>Constructed Nature.</strong> A possessed pillar doesn’t require air, food, drink, or sleep.<br>Content licensed under the @Compendium[koboldpressogl.koboldpressmonsters.KPOGL]{Open Game License}",
        "public": ""
